Nathan Hand wrote:
> Don't treat the -root user- like the idiot
> fool who needs their hand held.
But what if I want to treat the -root user- like a script kiddie who
needs their hand cut off?
Restricting useless actions is not a crime against root, and it gives
the real root user a few less things to check for after a compromise.
